The paper discusses a system architecture for performing privacy-preserving software monitoring and analytics, which involves cryptography and statistical techniques. This suggests that the paper could belong to the categories of "Cryptography and Security" (cs.CR), "Databases" (cs.DB), "Machine Learning" (cs.LG), "Computers and Society" (cs.CY), and "Social and Information Networks" (cs.SI). However, since the paper focuses on privacy-preserving analytics, cs.CR and cs.DB are the most likely categories, followed by cs.LG, cs.CY, and cs.SI.
